Create a new application named "echo" from the Dockerfile in the ubi-echo folder. 
Use the branch you created in a previous step. It creates, among other resources, a build configuration: 

oc new-app --name echo
    https://github.com/${RHT_OCP4_GITHUB_USER}/DO288-apps#docker-build 
    --context-dir ubi-echo
    
View logs
oc logs -f bc/echo

oc status
oc logs

cd /ubi-info
FROM registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8/ubi:8.0
USER 1001
CMD bash -c "while true; do (( i++ )); echo test \$i; sleep 5; done"

git commit -a -m 'Add a counter'
git push
cd ~

start-build
